dasanShdslMIB.name: dasanShdslMIB
dasanShdslMIB.description: The MIB module to describe G.SHDSL product. The MIB module that provides objects that are proprietary and extension to SHDSL- LINE-MIB. The MIB include extension to following Tables. The MIB also include a set of scalar(s) clubbed under the group 'dsShdslCapabilityGroup'.

dsShdslLineStatusTable.name: dsShdslLineStatusTable
dsShdslLineStatusTable.description: This MO is proprietary extension of RFC 3276 MIB and contains the proprietary line status.

dsShdslLineStatusEntry.name: dsShdslLineStatusEntry
dsShdslLineStatusEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the dsShdslLineStatusTable. The Table is indexed by ifIndex.

dsShdslOpState.name: dsShdslOpState
dsShdslOpState.description: This object identifies the high level operational state for the STU.

dsShdslStartProgress.name: dsShdslStartProgress
dsShdslStartProgress.description: This object identifies the current detailed operational state of the STU.

dsShdslLineSwap.name: dsShdslLineSwap
dsShdslLineSwap.description: This object indicates if the physical lines are swapped, i.e., logical channel A is connected to physical channel B. This applies to 4-wire operation only.

dsShdslRmtCountryCode.name: dsShdslRmtCountryCode
dsShdslRmtCountryCode.description: This object provides the country code word, as defined in ITU-T G.991.2, for the STU at the other end of the loop. GlobespanVirata sets this to USA.

dsShdslRmtEncoderA.name: dsShdslRmtEncoderA
dsShdslRmtEncoderA.description: This object identifies the 21-bit value corresponding to encoder coefficient A, as defined in ITU-T G.991.2, for the STU at the other end of the loop.

dsShdslRmtEncoderB.name: dsShdslRmtEncoderB
dsShdslRmtEncoderB.description: This object identifies the 21-bit value corresponding to encoder coefficient B, as defined in ITU-T G.991.2, for the STU at the other end of the loop.

dsShdslRmtProviderCode.name: dsShdslRmtProviderCode
dsShdslRmtProviderCode.description: This object identifies the provider code word, as defined in ITU-T G.991.2, for the STU at the other end of the loop.

dsShdslLocDetect.name: dsShdslLocDetect
dsShdslLocDetect.description: This object is used to determine if carrier has been lost.

dsShdslTxPower.name: dsShdslTxPower
dsShdslTxPower.description: This object identifies the local STU transmit power in tenths of a dBm.

dsShdslFramerSync.name: dsShdslFramerSync
dsShdslFramerSync.description: This object returns information regarding the framer synchronization status.

dsShdslRmtTomData.name: dsShdslRmtTomData
dsShdslRmtTomData.description: This object provides vendor-provided data, as defined in ITU-T G.991.2, for the STU at the other end of the loop.

dsShdslDriftAlarm.name: dsShdslDriftAlarm
dsShdslDriftAlarm.description: This object identifies if the receive clock is in or out of range.

dsShdslReceiverGain.name: dsShdslReceiverGain
dsShdslReceiverGain.description: This object provides the total receiver gain in dB.

dsShdslBertError.name: dsShdslBertError
dsShdslBertError.description: This object provides the count of bit errors since the last time the object was read, as well as the type of synchronization.

dsShdslFramerOHAndDefects.name: dsShdslFramerOHAndDefects
dsShdslFramerOHAndDefects.description: This object returns overhead data. The four least significant bits contain the overhead data in the following format: bit 0 is losd, bit 1 is sega, bit 2 is ps, and bit 3 is segd.

dsShdslRmtFwVersion.name: dsShdslRmtFwVersion
dsShdslRmtFwVersion.description: This object provides the transceiver firmware release number of the STU at the other end of the loop.

dsShdslUtopiaCellDelineation.name: dsShdslUtopiaCellDelineation
dsShdslUtopiaCellDelineation.description: This object indicates whether cell delineation has been found.

dsShdslUtopiaRxCellCnt.name: dsShdslUtopiaRxCellCnt
dsShdslUtopiaRxCellCnt.description: This object indicates the number of UTOPIA cells received since the last time the object has been called. The maximum value is 0xFFFF.

dsShdslUtopiaCellDropCnt.name: dsShdslUtopiaCellDropCnt
dsShdslUtopiaCellDropCnt.description: This object indicates the number of UTOPIA cells dropped since the last time the object has been called. The maximum value is 0xFF.

dsShdslUtopiaRxHecErrorCnt.name: dsShdslUtopiaRxHecErrorCnt
dsShdslUtopiaRxHecErrorCnt.description: This object indicates the number of UTOPIA cells with HEC errors since the last time the object has been called. The maximum value is 0xFF.

dsShdslUtopiaTxCellCnt.name: dsShdslUtopiaTxCellCnt
dsShdslUtopiaTxCellCnt.description: This object indicates the number of UTOPIA cells transmitted since the last time the object has been called. The maximum value is 0xFFFF.

dsShdslRmtNsfCusId.name: dsShdslRmtNsfCusId
dsShdslRmtNsfCusId.description: This object returns the customer identification that was sent by the STU at the other end of the loop.

dsShdslRmtNsfCusData.name: dsShdslRmtNsfCusData
dsShdslRmtNsfCusData.description: This object returns non-standard format customer data that was sent by the STU at the other end of the loop.

dsShdslLocalHandshake.name: dsShdslLocalHandshake
dsShdslLocalHandshake.description: This object provides a way to see what capabilities are supported by the local STU. A total of 26 handshake parameters are supported.

dsShdslRemoteHandshake.name: dsShdslRemoteHandshake
dsShdslRemoteHandshake.description: This object provides a way to see what capabilities are supported by the STU at the other end of the loop. A total of 26 handshake parameters are supported.

dsShdslActualHandshake.name: dsShdslActualHandshake
dsShdslActualHandshake.description: This object provides the results of capabilities exchanged during handshake. A total of 26 handshake parameters are supported.

dsShdslRmtTxPower.name: dsShdslRmtTxPower
dsShdslRmtTxPower.description: This object provides the transmit power of the STU at the other end of the loop.

dsShdslRmtPowerBackoff.name: dsShdslRmtPowerBackoff
dsShdslRmtPowerBackoff.description: This object indicates whether power backoff is enabled or disabled at the STU at the other end of the loop.

dsShdslAutoRetrainCount.name: dsShdslAutoRetrainCount
dsShdslAutoRetrainCount.description: This object indicates the number of automatic retrains. This counter is only reset when a startup is initiated.

dsShdslEocState.name: dsShdslEocState
dsShdslEocState.description: This object provides status information about the eoc stage.

dsShdslFramerOneSecondCnt.name: dsShdslFramerOneSecondCnt
dsShdslFramerOneSecondCnt.description: This object provides CRC, SEGA, and LOSW defect one second error counts, and should be called every second.

dsShdslNtrFault.name: dsShdslNtrFault
dsShdslNtrFault.description: This object identifies the Network Timing Recovery Fault.

dsShdslParametricTestResult.name: dsShdslParametricTestResult
dsShdslParametricTestResult.description: Indicates the Result of the Parametric Test conducted on the Xcvr.

dsShdslParametricTestArray.name: dsShdslParametricTestArray
dsShdslParametricTestArray.description: Conexant parameter that indicates the Parametric Test Array.

dsShdslLineParamsTable.name: dsShdslLineParamsTable
dsShdslLineParamsTable.description: This MO is proprietary extension of RFC 3276 MIB and contains the proprietary line parameters.

dsShdslLineParamsEntry.name: dsShdslLineParamsEntry
dsShdslLineParamsEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the dsShdslLineParamsTable. The Table is indexed by ifIndex.

dsShdslAction.name: dsShdslAction
dsShdslAction.description: This object specifies actions that are used to control transceiver operation.

dsShdslMode.name: dsShdslMode
dsShdslMode.description: This object specifies the operational mode of the transceiver.

dsShdslPowerScale.name: dsShdslPowerScale
dsShdslPowerScale.description: This object is used to compensate for minor differences in transmit power between designs.

dsShdslFramerType.name: dsShdslFramerType
dsShdslFramerType.description: This object defines which type of data interface type is used. Note that the non-default values only apply to Conexant chips that support serial interfaces.

dsShdslAFEType.name: dsShdslAFEType
dsShdslAFEType.description: This objects defines which AFE is being used.

dsShdslEncodeCoeffA.name: dsShdslEncodeCoeffA
dsShdslEncodeCoeffA.description: This object determines the value of encoder coefficient A, as defined in ITU-T G.991.2.

dsShdslEncodeCoeffB.name: dsShdslEncodeCoeffB
dsShdslEncodeCoeffB.description: This object determines the value of encoder coefficient B, as defined in ITU-T G.991.2

dsShdslTxEOCBufferLen.name: dsShdslTxEOCBufferLen
dsShdslTxEOCBufferLen.description: This object determines the number of bytes of EOC data that is buffered by the DSP in the transmit direction.

dsShdslRxEOCBufferLen.name: dsShdslRxEOCBufferLen
dsShdslRxEOCBufferLen.description: This object determines the number of bytes of EOC data that is buffered by the DSP in the receive direction.

dsShdslNTR.name: dsShdslNTR
dsShdslNTR.description: This object defines how network-timing recovery is performed.

dsShdslRxUpstreamFrameSync.name: dsShdslRxUpstreamFrameSync
dsShdslRxUpstreamFrameSync.description: Customer-defined value. This object defines the upstream frame sync word.

dsShdslRxDownstreamFrameSync.name: dsShdslRxDownstreamFrameSync
dsShdslRxDownstreamFrameSync.description: This object defines the downstream frame sync word.

dsShdslRxUpstreamStuffBits.name: dsShdslRxUpstreamStuffBits
dsShdslRxUpstreamStuffBits.description: Customer-defined value. This object defines the upstream.

dsShdslRxDownstreamStuffBits.name: dsShdslRxDownstreamStuffBits
dsShdslRxDownstreamStuffBits.description: This object defines the downstream stuff bits.

dsShdslInitiate.name: dsShdslInitiate
dsShdslInitiate.description: This object defines which STU initiates a startup. The default is STU-R initiates and STU-C waits.

dsShdslFramerRxClockMode.name: dsShdslFramerRxClockMode
dsShdslFramerRxClockMode.description: This object determines the source of the receive clock.

dsShdslFramerRxPllMode.name: dsShdslFramerRxPllMode
dsShdslFramerRxPllMode.description: This object enables or disables the internal PLL.

dsShdslSerialAtmCiuBufferSize.name: dsShdslSerialAtmCiuBufferSize
dsShdslSerialAtmCiuBufferSize.description: This object enables the user to set the size of the framer buffer for serial ATM operation.

dsShdslUtopiaL2TxAddress.name: dsShdslUtopiaL2TxAddress
dsShdslUtopiaL2TxAddress.description: This object selects the appropriate UTOPIA Level 2 address for the transmit interface.

dsShdslUtopiaL2RxAddress.name: dsShdslUtopiaL2RxAddress
dsShdslUtopiaL2RxAddress.description: This object selects the appropriate UTOPIA Level 2 address for the receive interface.

dsShdslTxFramerPulseDelay.name: dsShdslTxFramerPulseDelay
dsShdslTxFramerPulseDelay.description: This parameter is for Serial ATM applications only. It is recommended that the default value be used. For special customer configurations, a delay of up to 7 clock cycles can be specified for the transmit frame pulse.

dsShdslRxFramerPulseDelay.name: dsShdslRxFramerPulseDelay
dsShdslRxFramerPulseDelay.description: This parameter is for Serial ATM applications only. It is recommended that the default value be used. For special customer configurations, a delay of up to 7 clock cycles can be specified for the receive frame pulse.

dsShdslMultiFrameMode.name: dsShdslMultiFrameMode
dsShdslMultiFrameMode.description: This object specifies the multi frame operational mode of the transceiver.

dsShdslEnable4or6MbpsBitrate.name: dsShdslEnable4or6MbpsBitrate
dsShdslEnable4or6MbpsBitrate.description: This object specifies the operational state of the 4_6Mbps bit rate.

dsShdslTomDataWord1.name: dsShdslTomDataWord1
dsShdslTomDataWord1.description: This object identifies one of four words of proprietary vendor data, as described in the Vendor Data section of ITU-T G.994.1.bis.

dsShdslTomDataWord2.name: dsShdslTomDataWord2
dsShdslTomDataWord2.description: This object identifies one of four words of proprietary vendor data, as described in the Vendor Data section of ITU-T G.994.1.bis.

dsShdslTomDataWord3.name: dsShdslTomDataWord3
dsShdslTomDataWord3.description: This object identifies one of four words of proprietary vendor data, as described in the Vendor Data section of ITU-T G.994.1.bis.

dsShdslTomDataWord4.name: dsShdslTomDataWord4
dsShdslTomDataWord4.description: This object identifies one of four words of proprietary vendor data, as described in the Vendor Data section of ITU-T G.994.1.bis.

dsShdslSetReqSilenceMode.name: dsShdslSetReqSilenceMode
dsShdslSetReqSilenceMode.description: This object enables a silent mode for the STU at the opposite end of the loop for approximately one minute. During the silent period, the STU that requested the silent mode could perform whatever operations it wants and the STU at the opposite end will remain in handshake.

dsShdslSetIndividualRates1.name: dsShdslSetIndividualRates1
dsShdslSetIndividualRates1.description: This item enables the user to individually enable or disable base rates for N=1 through N=16. The default is all rates enabled.

dsShdslSetIndividualRates2.name: dsShdslSetIndividualRates2
dsShdslSetIndividualRates2.description: This item enables the user to individually enable or disable base rates for N=17 through N=32. The default is all rates enabled.

dsShdslSetIndividualRates3.name: dsShdslSetIndividualRates3
dsShdslSetIndividualRates3.description: This item enables the user to individually enable or disable base rates for N=33 through N=36. The default is all rates enabled.

dsShdslSatmCellDelineation.name: dsShdslSatmCellDelineation
dsShdslSatmCellDelineation.description: This object enables the user to enable or disable cell delineation for serial ATM operation. This parameter should be set before a startup.

dsShdslFramerCellDropOnError.name: dsShdslFramerCellDropOnError
dsShdslFramerCellDropOnError.description: This object determines whether cells are dropped, i.e., not passed to the host, or not dropped, i.e., passed to the host. This object must be set prior to startup.

dsShdslGearShiftType.name: dsShdslGearShiftType
dsShdslGearShiftType.description: This object specifies the Gear Shift Type.

dsShdslHsNsf.name: dsShdslHsNsf
dsShdslHsNsf.description: This object enables or disables nonstandard Information fields for MP, MS, CL, and CLR messages, as defined in ITU-T G.994.1.bis.

dsShdslHsMaxBitsPerBaud.name: dsShdslHsMaxBitsPerBaud
dsShdslHsMaxBitsPerBaud.description: This object specifies the maximum bit per baud.

dsShdslHsCusId.name: dsShdslHsCusId
dsShdslHsCusId.description: This object identifies the customer identification during handshaking, as described in ITU-T G.994.1.bis.

dsShdslHsCusData0.name: dsShdslHsCusData0
dsShdslHsCusData0.description: This object identifies two words of customer data during handshaking, as defined in ITU-T G.994.1.bis.

dsShdslHsCusData1.name: dsShdslHsCusData1
dsShdslHsCusData1.description: This object identifies two words of customer data during handshaking, as defined in ITU-T G.994.1.bis.

dsShdslHsAnnexBType.name: dsShdslHsAnnexBType
dsShdslHsAnnexBType.description: This object allows the customer to choose between support for Annex B, Annex B with Access Network Frequency Plan (ANFP), or both.

dsShdslArCrcCheck.name: dsShdslArCrcCheck
dsShdslArCrcCheck.description: Enables or disables auto-retrain based on CRC errors.

dsShdslArFramerSyncCheck.name: dsShdslArFramerSyncCheck
dsShdslArFramerSyncCheck.description: Enables or disables auto-retrain based on framer synchronization.

dsShdslArSnrMarginCheck.name: dsShdslArSnrMarginCheck
dsShdslArSnrMarginCheck.description: Enables or disables auto-retrain based on whether the S/N margin falls below a preset threshold.

dsShdslArCrcThreshold.name: dsShdslArCrcThreshold
dsShdslArCrcThreshold.description: Sets the threshold for the number of frames with CRC errors for autoretrain.

dsShdslArSnrMarginThreshold.name: dsShdslArSnrMarginThreshold
dsShdslArSnrMarginThreshold.description: Set the margin threshold for autoretrain.

dsShdslArRetrainTime.name: dsShdslArRetrainTime
dsShdslArRetrainTime.description: Sets the time over which the autoretrain parameters must be outside their normal ranges, so that an auto-retrain occurs.

dsShdslOpStateTrapEnable.name: dsShdslOpStateTrapEnable
dsShdslOpStateTrapEnable.description: Enables/disables trap indicating a change in op state.

dsShdslTxFrmrDataClkEdge.name: dsShdslTxFrmrDataClkEdge
dsShdslTxFrmrDataClkEdge.description: This parameter is for Serial ATM applications only. It is recommended that the default value be used. For special customer configurations, transmit data can be sampled upon either rising or falling edge of the transmit clock.

dsShdslRxFrmrDataClkEdge.name: dsShdslRxFrmrDataClkEdge
dsShdslRxFrmrDataClkEdge.description: This parameter is for Serial ATM applications only. It is recommended that the default value be used. For special customer configurations, receive data can be valid upon either rising or falling edge of the receive clock.

dsShdslTxFrmrPulseClkEdge.name: dsShdslTxFrmrPulseClkEdge
dsShdslTxFrmrPulseClkEdge.description: This parameter is for Serial ATM applications only. It is recommended that the default value be used. For special customer configurations, the transmit frame pulse can be active upon either rising or falling edge.

dsShdslRxFrmrPulseClkEdge.name: dsShdslRxFrmrPulseClkEdge
dsShdslRxFrmrPulseClkEdge.description: This parameter is for Serial ATM applications only. It is recommended that the default value be used. For special customer configurations, the transmit frame pulse can be active upon either rising or falling edge.

dsShdslTxFrmrPulseLvl.name: dsShdslTxFrmrPulseLvl
dsShdslTxFrmrPulseLvl.description: This parameter is for Serial ATM applications only. It is recommended that the default value be used. For special customer configurations, the transmit frame pulse can be either active high (1) or active low (0).

dsShdslRxFrmrPulseLvl.name: dsShdslRxFrmrPulseLvl
dsShdslRxFrmrPulseLvl.description: This parameter is for Serial ATM applications only. It is recommended that the default value be used. For special customer configurations, the transmit frame pulse can be either active high (1) or active low (0).

dsShdslUtopiaDataBusWidth.name: dsShdslUtopiaDataBusWidth
dsShdslUtopiaDataBusWidth.description: This parameter is used to specify width of UTOPIA data bus.

dsShdslFrmrOH.name: dsShdslFrmrOH
dsShdslFrmrOH.description: This object specifies framer OverHead Channel.

dsShdslLoopAttenCrossingTrapEnable.name: dsShdslLoopAttenCrossingTrapEnable
dsShdslLoopAttenCrossingTrapEnable.description: This Parameter enables or disables the Trap for Loop Attenuation Threshold crossing.

dsShdslSNRMarginCrossingTrapEnable.name: dsShdslSNRMarginCrossingTrapEnable
dsShdslSNRMarginCrossingTrapEnable.description: This Parameter enables or disables the Trap for SNR Margin Threshold crossing.

dsShdslFramerOHAndDefectsTrapEnable.name: dsShdslFramerOHAndDefectsTrapEnable
dsShdslFramerOHAndDefectsTrapEnable.description: This Parameter enables or disables the Trap for Framer Overhead and Defects.

dsShdslParametricTestInputFile.name: dsShdslParametricTestInputFile
dsShdslParametricTestInputFile.description: Indicates Name of the Input file from which to take the Mask Array Size, lower and upper mask Array. Null string means no file is specified.

dsShdslParamHybridLossTestStart.name: dsShdslParamHybridLossTestStart
dsShdslParamHybridLossTestStart.description: Indicates Start bin for range of bins to be measured. The default value mentioned is an indicative value only, for exact value refer to document number DO-400523-AN and DO-401163-AN.

dsShdslParamHybridLossTestEnd.name: dsShdslParamHybridLossTestEnd
dsShdslParamHybridLossTestEnd.description: Indicates End bin for range of bins to be measured. The default value mentioned is an indicative value only.

dsShdslSpanStatusExtnTable.name: dsShdslSpanStatusExtnTable
dsShdslSpanStatusExtnTable.description: This table is a proprietary extension of hdsl2ShdslSpanStatusTable

dsShdslSpanStatusExtnEntry.name: dsShdslSpanStatusExtnEntry
dsShdslSpanStatusExtnEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the dsShdslSpanStatusExtnTable. The Table is indexed by ifIndex.

dsShdslStatusPMMSMaxLineRate.name: dsShdslStatusPMMSMaxLineRate
dsShdslStatusPMMSMaxLineRate.description: This object provides the maximum PMMS rate the line is capable of achieving

dsShdslStatus4WireHsMode.name: dsShdslStatus4WireHsMode
dsShdslStatus4WireHsMode.description: Contains the current 4 Wire Handshake Mode Configured

dsShdslCapabilityLineTxCap.name: dsShdslCapabilityLineTxCap
dsShdslCapabilityLineTxCap.description: This bitmap specifies the transmission modes that the STU-C is capable of supporting. Right now, support for Annex A (q9921PotsNonOverlapped(2) and q9921PotsOverlapped(3)) is present. This value depends on the DSL PHY firmware present on Columbia MxU.
